  },
  {
    "id" : "786cc5a7-ead7-4d2c-b57c-4003f5a19456",
    "prId" : 8229,
    "prUrl" : "https://github.com/conda-forge/staged-recipes/pull/8229#pullrequestreview-276116337",
    "prSource" : "GitHub",
    "comments" : [
      {
        "id" : "ba1c9d30-e0d9-4dcc-8536-dd1fb1e4673a",
        "parentId" : null,
        "authorId" : "fa18c2b0-9128-4c2b-b6e0-433b177f7cf1",
        "body" : "You need the `run_exports` of the C++ compiler runtime here as well.",
        "createdAt" : "2019-08-16T18:00:35Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-08-16T19:05:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "fa18c2b0-9128-4c2b-b6e0-433b177f7cf1",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "11fde9b1-a584-49c5-a333-85893f431c15",
        "parentId" : "ba1c9d30-e0d9-4dcc-8536-dd1fb1e4673a",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "Why? If the user is using the C++ compiler, that will be added by this anyways.",
        "createdAt" : "2019-08-16T18:19:41Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-08-16T19:05:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "2443409c-8216-48ed-ba36-130871cc94ca",
        "parentId" : "ba1c9d30-e0d9-4dcc-8536-dd1fb1e4673a",
        "authorId" : "fa18c2b0-9128-4c2b-b6e0-433b177f7cf1",
        "body" : "But the runtimes like `libgcc-ng` and `libstdcxx-ng` will not be added. `run_exports` is not transitive.",
        "createdAt" : "2019-08-16T18:21:02Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-08-16T19:05:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "fa18c2b0-9128-4c2b-b6e0-433b177f7cf1",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "3193c27e-aaf9-4e49-b062-c8b122c59da1",
        "parentId" : "ba1c9d30-e0d9-4dcc-8536-dd1fb1e4673a",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "I don't think users should be relying on `nvcc` to add these things. If they are using a C or C++ compiler, they should list those requirements explicitly in their recipe.",
        "createdAt" : "2019-08-16T18:22:35Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-08-16T19:05:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "0678d85f-6033-4694-a962-196f9ec84342",
        "parentId" : "ba1c9d30-e0d9-4dcc-8536-dd1fb1e4673a",
        "authorId" : "fa18c2b0-9128-4c2b-b6e0-433b177f7cf1",
        "body" : "Then the C and C++ compiler should not be in run requirements. The way the compiler package is set up is that if the user tries to use a C++ compiler in the docker image, it will not be found if it is not an explicit requirement. Having the explicit requirement means that the `run_exports` for `libgcc-ng` is added.\r\nBut now, if the user adds `nvcc_linux-64`, they get the C++ compiler, but no `run_exports` for `libgcc-ng`.",
        "createdAt" : "2019-08-16T18:26:06Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-08-16T19:05:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "fa18c2b0-9128-4c2b-b6e0-433b177f7cf1",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "f7780df6-d10d-4468-8a4b-34c767e6fb1f",
        "parentId" : "ba1c9d30-e0d9-4dcc-8536-dd1fb1e4673a",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "That makes sense. Have dropped the C and C++ compiler from `run`. They won't be installed now. The test has been updated to list C and C++ as requirements of the test.",
        "createdAt" : "2019-08-16T18:55:36Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2019-08-16T19:05:47Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      }
    ],
